"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 17, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gca1665703174791.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gca1665703174791.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gca1665703174791.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gca1665703174791\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Indicates whether the specified ESMTP extension is supported.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gca1665703174791__section_w3724ab1b5b1_w3725ab1b5_w3726ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d272206e49\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">SMTP security drivers</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gca1665703174791__section_w3727ab1b5b3_w3728ab1b5_w3729ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d272206e58\">Expected Input</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132404e1_d132405e1_d132406e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Properties</code>,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">Parameters</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132407e1_d132408e1_d132409e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">InBuf</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">InDataLen</code>,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">InBufLen</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132410e1_d132411e1_d132412e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">DrvArea</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gca1665703174791__section_w3730ab1b5b5_w3731ab1b5_w3732ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d272206e88\">Expected Output</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132416e1_d132417e1_d132418e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsg</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsgLen</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132419e1_d132420e1_d132421e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">DrvArea</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gca1665703174791__section_w3733ab1b5b7_w3734ab1b5_w3735ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d272206e107\">Return Status</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132116e1_d132117e1_d132118e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_SUCCESS</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132119e1_d132120e1_d132121e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_ERROR</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gca1665703174791__section_w3736ab1b5b9_w3737ab1b5_w3738ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d272206e123\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132434e1_d132435e1_d132436e1\">This call must be implemented by SMTP security\n        drivers.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132437e1_d132438e1_d132439e1\">The caller of the API sends an <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"EHLO\"</code>\n        message to the SMTP server and stores the response of the supported extensions. The <code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mif1665703178050.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mif1665703178050.html\" title=\"Parses a line from a single-line or multi-line response from an SMTP server into the reply code and the associated message.\">ParseReply</a>\n</code> utility function can be used to parse this multi-line reply.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132440e1_d132441e1_d132442e1\">The list of supported extensions, pointed to by the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">InBuf</code> member and its length in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">InDataLen</code>, is passed\n        to the <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_VERIFY</code> function. The buffer contains each line as returned by\n        the SMTP server, starting with <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"250…\"</code> and ending with carriage return, line\n        feed. Typically the last line is <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"250 OK\"</code>. The driver must not modify the\n        contents of <code class=\"ph codeph\">InBuf</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gca1665703174791__p_d132443e1_d132444e1_d132445e1\">The driver must indicate if the extension is supported\n        or not with the return status <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_SUCCESS</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_ERROR</code>\n        respectively.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527796\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527796\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "USEC_VERIFY Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 17, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Indicates whether the specified ESMTP extension is supported. Use SMTP security drivers Expected Input Properties , Parameters InBuf , InDataLen , InBufLen DrvArea Expected Output ErrMsg , ErrMsgLen DrvArea Return Status USEC_SUCCESS USEC_ERROR Description This call must be implemented by SMTP security drivers. The caller of the API sends an \"EHLO\" message to the SMTP server and stores the response of the supported extensions. The ParseReply utility function can be used to parse this multi-line reply. The list of supported extensions, pointed to by the InBuf member and its length in the InDataLen , is passed to the USEC_VERIFY function. The buffer contains each line as returned by the SMTP server, starting with \"250…\" and ending with carriage return, line feed. Typically the last line is \"250 OK\" . The driver must not modify the contents of InBuf . The driver must indicate if the extension is supported or not with the return status USEC_SUCCESS or USEC_ERROR respectively. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}